Head pore at 0/1. Dorsal pores from VII. Spermathecal pores in ‘lateral lines’ at 4/5. Male pores as T-shaped slits with all three ‘arms’ of equal length (
Figure 7C
).

The material described comes exclusively from Naples, Capodimonte, plot N3 (sexually mature both in spring and autumn). According to some old notes, possibly also found in Erice (
Sicily
).
